<br>
Ok, can't let this go anymore.<br>
<br>
This is a false dicotomy.  <br>
<br>
Eq was never designed as a free form RP environment. That's a MOO.  In a Moo people can interact how they want as whatever they want, but it's purely consentual.  If you want to role-play a talking toaster while someone else role-plays a hologram of a dead low ranking military and someone else a race evolved from a mutated cat that is acceptable.  It's unstructured freeform, consentual improvisation aka role-play.<br>
<br>
FV is a role-playing game.  Role-playing games are designed enviornments with set limits on role-play.  Those involved are given options of what to play and a framework of how the world works.  Also the existence of game mechanics allow for a game to be played in and around the role-play. While they ultimately are consentual (in that people can largely choose to ignore others, at least in a PVE game) they are also designed to have a common framework all players accept so that all players may interact within one environment.<br>
<br>
Rules in RP games are not unfair restrictions on play.  They are safeguards to allow people to interact together without constant interuptions to re-establish the world's parameter.  The more people involved the more important these protections are. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eldratu>Eldratu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://img.villagephotos.com/p/2003-10/449185/eldratu6.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/5/03 4:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=66>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elven Blade Board BAN</span><hr size=1> To all that replied to this post:<br>
